@startuml
title Provider-Owned Graph Routing

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced

actor User
participant "domain/ui/ui_graph_editor\nGraph Canvas" as Graph
participant "domain/editor/editor_shell\nStructural route host" as Shell
participant "Concrete Provider\nmaterial / procgen / gameplay / animation" as Provider
participant "App Command Executor\napps/*" as App
participant "Owning Domain\nsource truth + ratification" as Domain
participant "Derived Projections\nand Products" as Products

User -> Graph : Interact with graph canvas
Graph -> Shell : GraphCanvasAction\nsemantic-free

note right of Graph
  GraphCanvasAction carries canvas intent only.
  It has no material, procgen, gameplay,
  animation, or physics semantics.
end note

Shell -> Provider : SurfaceLocalRoute + SurfaceInteraction\nToolSurfaceInstanceId + provider context

note right of Shell
  Shell hosts structure and route context.
  It does not branch on MaterialGraphCanvas,
  ProcgenGraphCanvas, GameplayGraphCanvas,
  AnimationGraphCanvas, or future graph semantics.
end note

Provider -> Provider : Map graph action using provider-local context
Provider -> App : Propose owning-domain command
App -> Domain : Execute through domain boundary
Domain -> Domain : Ratify and mutate source truth
Domain -> Products : Rebuild projections and formed products
Products -> Provider : Next observation/product inputs
Provider -> Shell : Next ResolvedSurfaceFrame

note bottom
  Future graph tools add concrete providers and route descriptors,
  not shell-level graph-tool routing branches.
end note

@enduml
